http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Farmer-ends-life/article14025713.ece

A debt-ridden farmer committed suicide by consuming pesticide at Nandihalli (J) village in Shahapur taluk of Yadgir district on Thursday.The farmer was identified as Ningayya Basappa Bolari (25) of the village. He had availed himself of around Rs. 8 lakh loan, including Rs. 1.50 lakh from banks, to develop six acres of land.According to sources, the farmer was upset after the cotton crop, which he had cultivated in the land, was damaged due to deficient rainfall.A case has been registered in the Shahapur Town Police Station.